| Problem from original | Fix in refactored |
|---|---|
| Hardcoded `DB_PATH`, `LOG_FILE`, credentials | `_get_config()` reads from env vars (`METRICS_DB_PATH`, `SERVER_LOG_PATH`, etc.) |
| SQL injection via `%` string formatting | All queries use `?` parameterized placeholders + `executemany` |
| One monolithic `proc_data()` function | 7 focused functions following ETL: `extract_logs` → `transform_errors`/`transform_api_latency` → `load_database`/`load_html_report` |
| `line.split(" ")` for parsing — fragile against extra spaces or new log formats | 4 compiled regex patterns (`_ERROR_RE`, `_INFO_USER_RE`, `_INFO_API_RE`, `_WARN_RE`) with named groups |
| No type hints or docstrings | Full type annotations + docstrings on every function |
| Unclosed file handles (`f = open(...)` / manual `f.close()`) | Context managers (`with open(...) as f`) throughout |
| Raw user content injected into HTML (XSS vector) | `_html_escape()` used in report generation |
